Codes identifying the stage lifecycle stage of the case
This code system http://fhir.hl7.org/us/case/CodeSystem/case-status defines the following codes:

tr.td: This is a partial (e.g. initial, interim or preliminary) case. Data may be incomplete or unverified.
Incomplete or unavailable because the case has been temporarily halted.
Incomplete or unavailable because the case was abandoned prior to completion.
Subsequent to being completed, the case has been reopened. This includes any change in the results, diagnosis, narrative text, or other content that has been issued.

This electronic record of this event should never have existed, though it is possible that real-world decisions were based on it. (If real-world activity has occurred, the status should be "cancelled" rather than "entered-in-error".)

The authoring system does not know which of the status values currently applies. Note: This concept is not to be used for "other" - one of the listed statuses is presumed to apply, it's just not known which one.

div.p: This is the draft trigger codes table. This list of codes is intended use is for filtering encounters in healthcare settings to screen for public health reportable conditions. It is intended to be used in the provider EHR system environment as lookup table to identify cases that should be forwarded to public healthas an intitial case report. The standard codes in this list are directed at diagnosis, laboratory results and laboratory order fro reportable conditions. Specifically it consist if ICD-10CM, SNOMED CT and LOINC codes. It may be expanded to include other code systems in future. It is derived from:1) The RKCMS tables list of code of which currently only for Chlamydia and Pertussis and Lead exist. 2) edited RCMT tables excluding out of scope and generic conditions 3) Cecil Lynch's Public Health Ontology. 4) CSTE's Technical Implementation Guides (TIG) documents. 5) ICD-10 Master Mapping Reference Table from ISDS. These codes are are deduplicated and sorted by code system. The list of conditions it encompasses is covered in the tab 'ConditionsCoveredbyCodeSystem' Tab [todo url for this].

description.value: This is the draft trigger codes table. This list of codes is intended use is for filtering encounters in healthcare settings to screen for public health reportable conditions. It is intended to be used in the provider EHR system environment as lookup table to identify cases that should be forwarded to public healthas an intitial case report. The standard codes in this list are directed at diagnosis, laboratory results and laboratory order fro reportable conditions. Specifically it consist if ICD-10CM, SNOMED CT and LOINC codes. It may be expanded to include other code systems in future. It is derived from:1) The RKCMS tables list of code of which currently only for Chlamydia and Pertussis and Lead exist. 2) edited RCMT tables excluding out of scope and generic conditions 3) Cecil Lynch's Public Health Ontology. 4) CSTE's Technical Implementation Guides (TIG) documents. 5) ICD-10 Master Mapping Reference Table from ISDS. These codes are are deduplicated and sorted by code system. The list of conditions it encompasses is covered in the tab 'ConditionsCoveredbyCodeSystem' Tab [todo url for this].
